
@startuml

' Define classes
class Location {
  +id: int
  +name: String
  +capacity: int
}

class Exhibition {
  +id: int
  +title: String
  +startDate: Date
  +endDate: Date
  +description: String
}

class Employee {
  +id: int
  +name: String
  +position: String
  +email: String
}

class ExhibitionItem {
  +id: int
  +name: String
  +description: String
  +required: boolean
}

class ArtPiece {
  +id: int
  +title: String
  +artist: String
  +yearCreated: int
  +medium: String
}

class Collector {
  +id: int
  +name: String
  +contactInfo: String
}

class Request {
  +id: int
  +status: String
  +requestDate: Date
  +approvedDate: Date (optional)
}

class CoachingRelationship {
  +startDate: Date
  +endDate: Date (optional)
}

' Relationships

Employee "1" -- "many" Exhibition : coordinates
Employee "1" -- "1" Employee : is coached by (via CoachingRelationship)

Exhibition "1" -- "many" ExhibitionItem : includes
ExhibitionItem "1" -- "many" Request : has
Request "1" -- "1" ArtPiece : requests
ArtPiece "1" -- "1" Collector : owned by

Location "1" -- "many" Exhibition : hosts

CoachingRelationship "1" -- "1" Employee : coach
CoachingRelationship "1" -- "1" Employee : junior

@enduml

---

### ✅ Explanation of Key Elements:

- **Location**: Represents areas in the museum where exhibitions can be hosted.
- **Exhibition**: A planned event at a location with a start/end date and items.
- **Employee**: Museum staff, including coordinators and coaches.
- **ExhibitionItem**: Required artifacts or themes for an exhibition.
- **ArtPiece**: Specific artwork requested from collectors.
- **Collector**: Individuals or institutions owning art pieces.
- **Request**: Link between an `ExhibitionItem` and a `Collector` to request an `ArtPiece`.
- **CoachingRelationship**: Tracks mentorship between senior and junior employees.

